        <item>
            <title>Hand Plane Basics - part 2 by Bill Rittner</title>
            <description>Now that all the parts of the #5 plane have been thoroughly cleaned, de-rusted and inspected, as can be seen in the photo above, it is time for the next step. All parts of the plane are shown in the photo except the knob and tote. These wood parts are being stripped and refinished and will be installed later.&lt;br /&gt;
The next thing that needs to be done is to determine that the sole of the plane is flat. This plane still shows the pattern of the original factory grinding so no work needs to be done to the sole or the sides. You can check the flatness of your plane’s sole using a good quality, (such as Browne &amp; Sharp or Starrett), steel scale, commonly called a rule, and a feeler gage.</description>
            <link>http://www.wkfinetools.com/contrib2/rittnerB/hpBasics/p2/hpBasics-04.asp</link>
