        <item>
            <title>Building a 19th Century-style Parlor Guitar, Part 2 – The Body  with Jason Stamper</title>
            <description>With the neck and headstock roughed out I moved on to making the body of the guitar. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The first thing I did was to plane the material down to the correct thickness on my thickness planer. Then I joined the top and back pieces up. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I did this by putting a ruler under the joint on a piece of plywood and then clamping the outside edges down while keeping the joint tight. Once the edge clamps were in place I pulled the ruler out and pressed the center seam down with a caul and more clamps.</description>
            <link>http://www.wkfinetools.com/contrib2/stamperJ/parlorGuitar/parlorGuitar-04.asp</link>
